The paper deals with algorithms for finding separators in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of dynamic approximate distance oracles suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem of finding separators is closely related to computational geometry, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category. The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) categories. Finally, the use of numerical methods for solving optimization problems suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category.
